On January 30, 2009, President Obama declared a major disaster in the State of Washington due to a severe winter storm, landslides, mudslides, and flooding that occurred from January 6-16, 2009. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Nancy Ward, Acting Administrator of FEMA, named Willie G. Nunn as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by phone. The toll-free telephone numbers will be available seven days a week from 8 a.m. to 6 p.m. local time.